    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Campylotropis stenocarpa are diarrhea, inflammation, fever reduction, and gastroenteritis, which the plant treats by reducing fluid loss and electrolyte imbalance. It also helps alleviate rheumatism through its anti-inflammatory properties, reducing joint swelling and pain. Additionally, Campylotropis stenocarpa has been used to heal wounds by promoting tissue repair and collagen synthesis, and to treat dysentery through antimicrobial activity, reducing the severity of diarrhea and inflammation. Furthermore, it has been used to alleviate cough, asthma, skin irritation, hypertension, diabetes, anemia, colic, nausea, malaria, cholera, infection, and skin infections due to its antispasmodic, expectorant, and antihypertensive properties, as well as its ability to stimulate appetite and improve nutrition. By promoting wound healing, reducing inflammation, and treating various infections, Campylotropis stenocarpa offers a wide range of therapeutic applications.",
