    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Campylotropis stenocarpa improperly include experiencing nausea, cause diarrhea, inducing nausea, experiencing vomiting, and developing skin irritation. These side effects can occur due to the plant's toxic compounds, specifically the presence of flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins, which can cause gastrointestinal disturbances and skin reactions. When ingested in large quantities or without proper preparation, Campylotropis stenocarpa can lead to these adverse effects. Additionally, improper use of the plant can also cause allergic reactions and irritation to the skin, eyes, and mucous membranes. It is essential to consult with a healthcare professional or a qualified herbalist before using Campylotropis stenocarpa to minimize the risk of side effects.",
